\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 This lab is part of Kaggle's 
\f1\b 5-Day AI Agents: Intensive Vibe Coding Course with Google
\f0\b0 . You can find the additional codelabs and resources available on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/5-day-ai-agents-intensive-vibecoding-course-with-google"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 event site}}.\
In this codelab, you will build a retail web application with an integrated AI Shopping Assistant using 
\f1\b Google's Agent Development Kit (ADK)
\f0\b0 . You will use 
\f1\b Google Antigravity IDE
\f0\b0  (Google's agentic IDE) to establish a secure, test-driven development (TDD) workflow.\
Rather than treating security as a late-stage gate, you will learn to "shift security left" to the point of code inception. You will enforce development standards, automate {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://owasp.org/www-community/Threat_Modeling_Process#stride-threat--mitigation-techniques"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 STRIDE threat modeling}}, and gate agent actions with git pre-commit hooks and agent-specific execution hooks.\
