\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 5. Create Project-Specific Rules}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To prevent overloading your agent's active memory with thousands of pages of generic security documentation\'97which causes context rot and reasoning latency, you must establish a "paved road" of pre-approved secure conventions. In Antigravity IDE, you can establish these guardrails by creating a persistent context file.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 Create a customization directory named `shopping-assistant/.agents` and\
create a file `shopping-assistant/.agents/CONTEXT.md` defining our secure\
coding standards:\
\
# Local Project Context & Secure Coding Standards\
\
## Core Paved Roads\
We systematically address common vulnerability classes by guiding the agent\
to use our pre-configured, secure-by-default helper patterns instead of\
writing raw implementation logic from scratch.\
\
1. **Tool Input Validation**: Every agent tool must validate incoming\
\'a0 \'a0parameters against strict Pydantic schemas rather than parsing raw\
\'a0 \'a0dictionaries or strings.\
2. **No Shell Execution**: Never use `run_command` or raw shell execution\
\'a0 \'a0tools unless explicitly approved by `hooks.json`.\
3. **Pre-Commit Remediation Loop**: If a git commit fails due to a pre-commit\
\'a0 \'a0hook error (such as a Semgrep scan finding), you MUST treat the violation\
\'a0 \'a0as a refactoring task, apply targeted fixes, run tests to verify no\
\'a0 \'a0regressions, and attempt to commit again.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 What to expect:
\f0\b0  Antigravity will create the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 .agents/
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  directory and the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 CONTEXT.md
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  file, displaying it directly in the auxiliary pane for your review.\

\f1\b Caution:
\f0\b0  Failing to centralize these rules causes the agent to fall back on basic training data, which might result in vulnerable string concatenation or open redirect vectors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/secure-agentic-coding#5"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 6. Configure Local Gating Hooks}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To prevent insecure code or secrets from ever leaving your workstation, configure automated gates at the boundaries of your development environment 
\f2\i \strokec2 before
\f0\i0 \strokec2  committing code. We will prompt Antigravity to generate the hook configurations, then install them using the terminal.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 1. Git Pre-Commit Hook\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To ensure our static analysis reliably catches simulated credentials and blocks insecure commits, we will define a custom Semgrep rule and configure a Git pre-commit hook to enforce it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Define a Custom Semgrep Rule\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Default Semgrep rules (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 --config auto
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) do not flag mock keys containing words like 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 "mock"
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  or hyphens due to low-confidence scoring. To reliably detect our hardcoded API key, we will create a custom local rules file utilizing direct regex scanning instead of generic rules.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 Create a custom Semgrep rules file `shopping-assistant/.semgrep/rules.yaml`\
with a rule to detect hardcoded Google API key prefixes (matching regex\
`AIzaSy[A-Za-z0-9_\\-]*`). Configure it for Python files with an error severity\
and a clear security warning message.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 What to expect:
