\f0\b0  The 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 --error
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  flag is 
\f1\b critical
\f0\b0 ; without it, Semgrep will log the security finding to standard output but return exit code 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 0
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  (success by default), which allows the unsafe commit to pass. Pre-commit only blocks commits on non-zero exit codes.\
